<!-- Title -->
VR Controlled Robot Arm
<!-- Content -->
<div class="main">
  <div class="title">VR Controlled Robot Arm</div>

  <div class="gallery">
    <div>
      <div class="heading">What did I build?</div>

      <p>
        I built a 4-DoF robotic arm (excluding end effector) with a claw gripper which has the ability to be controlled using a virtual reality controller. This
        allows the operator to use their intuitive spacial awareness to directly adjust the end effector position in real time.
      </p>

      <p>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/Lachlanric/Robot-Arm-Snatcha/tree/main">https://github.com/Lachlanric/Robot-Arm-Snatcha/tree/main</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="primary-image-container">
      <img class="gallery-image image-landscape" src="./img/1-robot-arm/Thumbnail.png" alt="Auto Wah Pedal" />
    </div>

    <div>
      <div class="heading">Key Technical Skills</div>

      <ul>
        <li>3D Design - Solidworks</li>
        <li>Laser cutting</li>
        <li>PCB Design - KiCad</li>
        <li>Surface mount soldering</li>
        <li>Kinematic modelling</li>
        <li>STM32 microcontroller programming</li>
        <li>Virtual reality programming - Unity Game Engine</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

